cket object increments/decrements. (b) Integration test multiple concurrent `call()` invocations through library entrypoint sharing one client/account context. Lower-level miss: shared-state wiring bugs (per-caller accidental bucket instantiation, context scoping errors) only appear when modules are exercised together under concurrency. Rejected higher level: System is disqualified because behavior text is explicitly 'same process' and can be reproduced with in-process async concurrency and stubs.","test_description":"Launch N concurrent `call()` promises on one client/account; use deterministic stub responses and inspect quota consumption/accounting to confirm all requests compete against one shared bucket (not per-request buckets).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When multiple requests are waiting to be sent, they are dispatched in the order they were originally submitted.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Candidate tests: (a) Unit test queue data structure FIFO behavior. (b) Integration test submission via public `call()` with quota pressure causing queueing, then releases that trigger dispatch. Lower-level miss: even with a correct FIFO queue unit test, dispatcher/scheduler integration can reorder sends (e.g., race in wake-up logic) so end-to-end dispatch order breaks. Rejected higher level: System is disqualified because ordering guarantees can be validated with in-process async control and fake timers; no real network/OS primitive is required by behavior text.","test_description":"Submit multiple calls quickly while quota prevents immediate send; then simulate quota availability and assert transport send order matches submission order exactly.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.13,"Integration":0.79,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
